WEBVTT

1
00:00:12.623 --> 00:00:15.058
Have you every had to break your family's rules?
你们有没有必须打破家庭规则的经历？

2
00:00:16.080 --> 00:00:18.614
Today, I'm breaking mine,
今天，我就要打破我的家中

3
00:00:18.638 --> 00:00:21.939
around money, secrecy and shame.
关于金钱，秘密和羞耻的规则。

4
00:00:23.742 --> 00:00:27.583
In 2006, on my brother Keith's 40th birthday, he called.
2006年，在我哥哥基斯 40岁生日那天，他打电话给我。

5
00:00:28.837 --> 00:00:31.392
"Tam, I'm in dire straits.
“塔米，我现在处境艰难。

6
00:00:32.334 --> 00:00:35.087
I wouldn't ask unless I had to.
不到万不得已，我不会开口的。

7
00:00:36.201 --> 00:00:38.643
Can I borrow 7,500 dollars?"
我能借7500美元吗？“

8
00:00:40.431 --> 00:00:43.185
This wasn't the first time he needed quick cash,
这不是他第一次急需用钱了，

9
00:00:43.209 --> 00:00:45.534
but this time, his voice frightened me.
但这次，他的声音吓到了我。

10
00:00:47.484 --> 00:00:51.547
I had never heard him so beaten down and shameful,
我从来没听过他这么沮丧和羞愧，

11
00:00:54.141 --> 00:00:56.228
and it was on his 40th birthday.
而且是在他40岁生日那天。

12
00:01:01.543 --> 00:01:04.471
After a few basic questions that we would all ask,
在问了几个我们通常会问的问题后，

13
00:01:05.557 --> 00:01:09.050
I agreed to loan him the money, but under one condition:
我同意借他钱，但有一个条件：

14
00:01:10.241 --> 00:01:12.685
that as the financial professional in the family,
作为家庭的财务专家，

15
00:01:12.709 --> 00:01:14.663
I wanted to meet with him and his wife
我想要见他和他的妻子，

16
00:01:14.687 --> 00:01:16.613
to see what was really happening.
了解一下到底发生了什么。

17
00:01:17.803 --> 00:01:21.026
Weeks later, we met at the local Starbucks,
几周后，我们在本地的星巴克见了面，

18
00:01:21.050 --> 00:01:25.247
and I started right in with the tough-love budget conversation.
然后我就开始了一场强硬的预算对话。

19
00:01:26.156 --> 00:01:30.435
"You should sell the house, downsize to something you can afford,
“你们应该卖掉房子， 精简到能负担得起的东西，

20
00:01:30.459 --> 00:01:32.425
sell the toys.
卖掉玩具，

21
00:01:32.449 --> 00:01:33.935
And Starbucks?
咖啡吗？

22
00:01:33.959 --> 00:01:35.959
Give up the five-dollar-a-day coffee."
不要再每天花5美元买咖啡了。“

23
00:01:37.163 --> 00:01:40.974
You know, all the trappings that we do to keep up with the Joneses.
这些都是爱慕虚荣导致的后果。

24
00:01:42.631 --> 00:01:45.870
Quickly, my brother and his wife went into a fearsome blame game,
很快，我哥哥和嫂子陷入了 一场可怕的责备漩涡，

25
00:01:47.168 --> 00:01:48.457
and it got messy.
事情开始变得一发不可收拾。

26
00:01:49.529 --> 00:01:54.409
I vacillated between therapist and pissed-off sister.
我在治疗师和被激怒的妹妹 角色之间摇摆不定。

27
00:01:55.849 --> 00:01:57.912
I wanted them to be better than this.
我想要他们过得更好。

28
00:01:58.320 --> 00:02:01.190
"Come on, you two. Get your shit together.
“得了，你俩，一起振作起来，

29
00:02:01.845 --> 00:02:03.351
You're parents.
都为人父母了。

30
00:02:03.375 --> 00:02:05.740
Grow up and buck up."
醒醒吧，振作起来。”

31
00:02:08.100 --> 00:02:10.621
After we left, I called my mom,
我们离开后，我打电话给母亲，

32
00:02:12.304 --> 00:02:14.234
but Keith beat me to it,
但基斯抢先了，

33
00:02:14.258 --> 00:02:16.645
and he told her that I wasn't helpful.
他告诉她我帮不上忙。

34
00:02:17.775 --> 00:02:21.235
In fact, he was hurt and felt ganged-up on.
事实上，他很受伤， 感觉没人站在他那一边。

35
00:02:24.020 --> 00:02:30.620
Of course he did. I shamed him with my tough-love budget conversation.
确实如此，我用强硬的 预算对话羞辱了他。

36
00:02:32.911 --> 00:02:35.427
Two months went by when I received a call.
两个月后，我接到个电话。

37
00:02:36.489 --> 00:02:39.070
"Tam? I have bad news.
“塔米，有个坏消息。

38
00:02:40.466 --> 00:02:42.529
Keith committed suicide last night."
基斯昨晚自杀了。“

39
00:02:47.567 --> 00:02:51.241
Days later, at his home, I went looking for answers,
几天后，在他家，我想要找到答案，

40
00:02:52.446 --> 00:02:54.631
in his "office" -- the garage.
在他的“办公室”——车库。

41
00:02:56.236 --> 00:03:00.467
There, I found a stack of overdue credit card bills
在那儿，我发现了一堆 过期的信用卡账单，

42
00:03:00.491 --> 00:03:05.181
and a foreclosure notice served to him on the day that he died.
和一张他自杀那天收到的止赎通知。

43
00:03:24.779 --> 00:03:29.308
My brother left behind his beautiful 10-year-old daughter,
我的哥哥留下了他美丽的10岁女儿，

44
00:03:29.332 --> 00:03:34.673
his brilliant 18-year-old son, weeks before his high school graduation,
以及一个聪明的儿子，已经18岁了， 几个星期后就要高中毕业，

45
00:03:34.697 --> 00:03:36.347
and his wife of 20 years.
还有相伴20年的妻子。

46
00:03:38.000 --> 00:03:39.396
How did this happen?
为什么会发生这样的事？

47
00:03:42.096 --> 00:03:46.676
My brother was caught in our family's money-shame cycle,
我哥哥受困于家庭财务羞耻的循环，

48
00:03:46.700 --> 00:03:48.794
and he was far from alone in this.
而这样的人远不止他一个。

49
00:03:49.907 --> 00:03:55.337
Suicide rates among adults ages 40 to 64
40到64岁的中年人，自杀率

50
00:03:55.361 --> 00:03:59.066
have risen nearly 40 percent since 1999.
自1999年来上升了近40%。

51
00:03:59.961 --> 00:04:03.493
Job loss, bankruptcy and foreclosures
失业、破产和丧失房屋抵押赎回权

52
00:04:03.517 --> 00:04:06.730
were present in nearly 40 percent of the deaths,
出现在40%的死亡案例中，

53
00:04:06.754 --> 00:04:12.143
with white middle-aged men accounting for seven out of 10 suicides.
10个自杀的人中， 就有7个是中年白人男性。

54
00:04:13.643 --> 00:04:15.834
What I've learned
我所了解的是，

55
00:04:15.858 --> 00:04:22.480
is that our self-destructive and self-defeating financial behaviors
我们的自我毁灭和挫败的财务行为

56
00:04:22.504 --> 00:04:26.405
are not driven by our rational, logical minds.
并不是由我们理性、 合乎逻辑的头脑所驱动的。

57
00:04:27.254 --> 00:04:33.548
Instead, they are a product of our subconscious belief systems
相反，它们是我们潜意识 信念系统的产物，

58
00:04:33.572 --> 00:04:35.763
rooted in our childhoods
根植于我们的童年，

59
00:04:35.787 --> 00:04:38.271
and so deeply ingrained in us,
根深蒂固地跟随着我们。

60
00:04:38.295 --> 00:04:43.176
they shape the way that we deal with money our entire adult lives,
它们塑造了我们整个成年生活 处理金钱的方式，

61
00:04:43.200 --> 00:04:49.429
and so many of you are left believing that you're lazy,
你们中很多人都认为自己很懒，

62
00:04:49.453 --> 00:04:53.653
crazy or stupid -- or just bad with money.
疯狂或不够聪明——或者不善赚取钱财。

63
00:04:54.847 --> 00:04:57.458
This is what I call money shame.
这就是我所说的金钱羞耻。

64
00:04:59.036 --> 00:05:02.723
Dr. Brené Brown, a well-known shame researcher,
布勒内 · 布朗博士， 是位知名的羞耻研究者，

65
00:05:02.747 --> 00:05:09.049
defines shame as "the intensely painful feeling or experience
把羞耻定义为“相信我们是有缺陷的，

66
00:05:09.073 --> 00:05:12.398
of believing that we are flawed,
因此不值得拥有爱和归属感的，

67
00:05:12.422 --> 00:05:16.001
and therefore unworthy of love and belonging."
极度痛苦的感觉或经历。”

68
00:05:17.566 --> 00:05:21.832
Based on this definition, here's how I'm defining money shame:
基于他的定义， 这是我所定义的金钱羞耻：

69
00:05:23.319 --> 00:05:26.002
"the intensely painful feeling or experience
“相信我们是有缺陷的，

70
00:05:26.026 --> 00:05:28.822
of believing that we are flawed,
因此不值得拥有爱和归属感的，

71
00:05:28.846 --> 00:05:32.011
and therefore unworthy of love and belonging,
极度痛苦的感觉或经历，

72
00:05:32.035 --> 00:05:34.257
based on our bank account balances,
基于我们的银行账户余额，

73
00:05:35.366 --> 00:05:39.914
our debts, our homes, our cars
我们的负债，我们的家庭，我们的汽车

74
00:05:39.938 --> 00:05:41.389
and our job titles."
以及我们的工作头衔。“

75
00:05:43.653 --> 00:05:46.241
Let me give you a couple of examples of what I mean.
我来举例说明我的意思。

76
00:05:47.576 --> 00:05:50.203
I believe that we all have money shame,
我认为我们都有金钱羞耻，

77
00:05:50.227 --> 00:05:54.122
whether you earn 10,000 dollars a year or 10 million,
不管你每年赚1万美金还是1千万美金，

78
00:05:54.146 --> 00:05:57.457
and it's because we give money all of our power.
这是因为我们把所有权力都给了钱。

79
00:05:59.557 --> 00:06:03.748
Here's what it would look like if someone that you love, or you,
如果你爱的人或你有金钱羞耻，

80
00:06:03.772 --> 00:06:05.896
might have money shame.
就可能会有这样的表现。

81
00:06:05.920 --> 00:06:09.250
They play the big shot, always picking up the check,
他们扮大款，总是主动签单，

82
00:06:09.274 --> 00:06:12.123
financially rescuing family and friends.
给予家人和朋友金钱上的帮助。

83
00:06:12.147 --> 00:06:14.401
They are financially secure,
他们在经济上是安全的，

84
00:06:14.425 --> 00:06:18.099
but they live in a state of chronic not-enoughness.
但长期生活在不充裕的状态。

85
00:06:20.253 --> 00:06:26.713
They drive a Mercedes, but their budget really only can afford a Honda.
他们开奔驰车，但实际预算 只能买得起一辆本田车。

86
00:06:28.054 --> 00:06:31.211
And they're looking good at every cost.
花出去的每一笔钱， 好像对生活都没什么影响。

87
00:06:32.359 --> 00:06:36.661
I know that we can break free from the grips of money shame,
我知道我们可以摆脱金钱的束缚，

88
00:06:36.685 --> 00:06:37.874
because I did.
因为我就有过这样的经历。

89
00:06:39.087 --> 00:06:42.777
Shortly after my brother's death, the Recession hit.
在我哥哥死后不久，经济衰退就开始了。

90
00:06:43.796 --> 00:06:46.853
I lost my business and faced bankruptcy.
我丢掉了生意并面临破产。

91
00:06:48.267 --> 00:06:52.028
Secretly, I was terrified.
私下说，我被吓到了。

92
00:06:53.229 --> 00:06:58.896
I stayed in my home for a year, thinking I did something wrong,
我在家里呆了整整一年， 总想着我把事情搞砸了，

93
00:06:58.920 --> 00:07:02.427
told myself, "What did you do? What happened?"
不停自问，“你到底做了什么？ 究竟发生了什么？”

94
00:07:03.672 --> 00:07:08.957
I stayed silent, while all along, I went outside and smiled.
我保持沉默，但自始至终， 我走到外面都面带微笑。

95
00:07:09.587 --> 00:07:10.737
Nobody knew.
没人知道我内心经历着什么——

96
00:07:11.512 --> 00:07:12.833
That's money shame.
那是金钱羞耻。

97
00:07:14.460 --> 00:07:19.818
So what I had to do was let go of the grip that I had
所以我要做的就是承认

98
00:07:19.842 --> 00:07:21.841
on knowing all the answers.
自己也会犯错误。

99
00:07:21.865 --> 00:07:23.745
I was the know-it-all in my family,
我曾是家里的万事通，

100
00:07:25.420 --> 00:07:29.992
and I had to give up the idea that a new financial plan
我不得不放弃一个新的财务计划

101
00:07:30.016 --> 00:07:31.372
was the solution.
是解决方案的这个想法。

102
00:07:33.008 --> 00:07:38.279
And so just like everything in my life, for me,
就像我生活中的一切，

103
00:07:38.303 --> 00:07:41.534
I was sent a human to help,
有人被派来帮助我，

104
00:07:42.716 --> 00:07:44.366
and I accepted the help,
我接受了帮助，

105
00:07:45.858 --> 00:07:49.153
but I had to do major self-inquiry
但是我必须对我家庭的金钱历史

106
00:07:49.177 --> 00:07:52.414
about my family's money history
和我的金钱理念

107
00:07:52.438 --> 00:07:54.304
and my money beliefs.
进行重大的自我反省。

108
00:07:56.597 --> 00:08:00.566
We have to start having this conversation.
我们必须开始进行这样的对话。

109
00:08:00.590 --> 00:08:03.271
Money can no longer be a taboo topic.
金钱不再是一个禁忌话题。

110
00:08:04.022 --> 00:08:10.126
We have to get honest with each other that we're suffering with money issues,
我们必须诚实地对待彼此，承认 我们正受到金钱问题的困扰，

111
00:08:10.150 --> 00:08:14.578
and let's get real -- we have to stop numbing out our pain.
让我们现实一点——我们必须 停止假装万事大吉。

112
00:08:16.304 --> 00:08:19.353
In order to uncover the painful parts
要揭开你的金钱故事

113
00:08:19.377 --> 00:08:22.118
of your money story and your money history,
和金钱历史的痛苦伤疤，

114
00:08:23.301 --> 00:08:24.594
you can't be numb.
你不能再麻木不仁了。

115
00:08:25.818 --> 00:08:31.000
We have to let go of our past in order to be free.
为了获得自由，我们必须放弃过去。

116
00:08:32.643 --> 00:08:36.334
Letting go of the past happens through surrender,
放弃过去是通过投降，

117
00:08:36.358 --> 00:08:38.341
faith and forgiveness.
信仰和宽恕来实现的。

118
00:08:39.154 --> 00:08:44.003
Debt is the tangible manifestation of not forgiving.
债是不宽恕的有形表现。

119
00:08:44.713 --> 00:08:48.920
If you have debt, you've not completely forgiven your past,
如果你有负债，你就还没有 完全原谅你的过去，

120
00:08:48.944 --> 00:08:52.704
so it's our work to forgive ourselves and others
所以我们的工作就是原谅自己和他人，

121
00:08:52.728 --> 00:08:54.490
so that we can live freely.
这样我们才能活得自由。

122
00:08:54.514 --> 00:08:57.743
Otherwise, our history will continue to repeat.
否则，我们的历史就会一次次重演。

123
00:08:59.468 --> 00:09:03.532
This is not a quick fix, and I know we all want one,
这不是一个快速的解决方案， 我知道我们都想走捷径，

124
00:09:03.556 --> 00:09:05.484
but it's a slow wake-up.
但这是一种缓慢的觉醒。

125
00:09:05.508 --> 00:09:07.873
This is another level of work.
这是另一个层次的工作。

126
00:09:08.233 --> 00:09:11.524
We have to go higher to get it,
我们必须更上一层楼才能得到它，

127
00:09:11.548 --> 00:09:12.817
to get at it.
去解决它。

128
00:09:13.834 --> 00:09:16.580
So try this: follow your dollars.
试试这个方法：记账。

129
00:09:17.122 --> 00:09:20.350
Your money will show you right away what you value.
你的钱会立刻显示出你的价值。

130
00:09:21.311 --> 00:09:22.788
Where's it going?
它去哪儿了？

131
00:09:22.812 --> 00:09:27.314
And then ask yourself: Do I really value all this stuff?
然后问你自己：我真的 很重视这些东西吗？

132
00:09:27.810 --> 00:09:31.229
And get curious about what you're feeling when you're spending.
在花钱的时候留意自己的感受。

133
00:09:31.253 --> 00:09:32.850
Are you lonely?
你感到孤单吗？

134
00:09:32.874 --> 00:09:34.206
Are you bored?
你感到无聊吗？

135
00:09:34.688 --> 00:09:37.299
Or are you just excited?
或者你只是觉得激动？

136
00:09:39.244 --> 00:09:41.553
But there's deeper work that needs to happen.
但还有更深层的工作需要去做。

137
00:09:41.883 --> 00:09:44.771
How did you get all these money beliefs to begin with?
你的这些财务观是怎么来的？

138
00:09:46.443 --> 00:09:49.203
I call this your money autobiography,
我把这叫做你的金钱自传，

139
00:09:49.227 --> 00:09:53.504
and as a money coach, this is the first step I take with my clients.
作为金钱教练， 这是我跟客户交谈的第一步。

140
00:09:54.593 --> 00:09:57.783
Think back to your earliest childhood money memory.
回想一下你童年时的金钱记忆。

141
00:09:58.505 --> 00:10:00.608
What did it feel like when you got money?
当你拿到钱的时候，感觉怎么样？

142
00:10:01.055 --> 00:10:04.858
Were you excited, proud or confused?
你是激动，骄傲还是迷惑？

143
00:10:05.871 --> 00:10:07.968
And what did you do with the money?
你都用钱做什么了？

144
00:10:07.992 --> 00:10:11.690
Did you run with the candy store, or did you run to the bank?
你是去糖果店了，还是存银行了？

145
00:10:12.719 --> 00:10:15.183
And what did you hear your parents say,
你听到父母说了什么，

146
00:10:15.207 --> 00:10:18.286
and what did you see your parents do with the money?
看到他们如何对待金钱了吗？

147
00:10:19.368 --> 00:10:21.588
My brother and I heard,
我哥哥和我听到过，

148
00:10:21.612 --> 00:10:23.469
"More money will make us happy."
“更多的钱会让我们幸福。”

149
00:10:24.326 --> 00:10:25.517
Every day.
每天都能听到。

150
00:10:25.541 --> 00:10:27.750
"More money will make us happy."
“更多的钱会让我们幸福。”

151
00:10:27.774 --> 00:10:31.201
And we internalized that into the money belief
当我们看到母亲生活在 长期的不充裕状态中，

152
00:10:31.225 --> 00:10:35.013
that our self worth was equal to our net worth
就会将其内化到我们的金钱信念中，

153
00:10:35.037 --> 00:10:40.334
as we watched our mom live in a state of chronic not-enoughness.
那就是，我们的自我价值 等于我们的净资产。

154
00:10:40.884 --> 00:10:45.026
And she numbed the pain with sugar and shopping.
她用糖和购物逃避痛苦。

155
00:10:46.261 --> 00:10:47.693
So what did we do?
我们又是怎么做的呢？

156
00:10:48.761 --> 00:10:50.793
Keith played out my mother's life.
基斯上演了我母亲的人生。

157
00:10:51.334 --> 00:10:55.325
He was an underearner, longed to be financially rescued,
他收入不足，渴望得到经济上的拯救，

158
00:10:55.349 --> 00:10:57.674
and he numbed out the pain with alcohol.
用酒精自我麻醉。

159
00:10:58.878 --> 00:11:00.206
I did the opposite.
我则相反。

160
00:11:01.180 --> 00:11:03.333
I became a high earner,
我成了一个高收入者，

161
00:11:03.357 --> 00:11:06.691
rescuer,
救助者，

162
00:11:06.715 --> 00:11:10.198
and I numbed the pain out with self-help books.
我用励志书籍来麻醉自己。

163
00:11:11.519 --> 00:11:14.345
But what we had in common was our money belief.
但我们有着共同的金钱信念。

164
00:11:14.369 --> 00:11:16.986
We both believed that our bank account balance
我们都相信我们的银行存款余额

165
00:11:17.010 --> 00:11:18.701
was equal to our self worth.
等于我们的自我价值。

166
00:11:20.724 --> 00:11:23.867
Looking back at the Starbucks meeting with my brother ...
回头再看我和哥哥在星巴克的会面…

167
00:11:25.423 --> 00:11:28.583
he didn't need a budget and my judgment.
他不需要做预算，也不需要我的评判。

168
00:11:29.512 --> 00:11:32.608
He needed a breakthrough from his suffering,
他需要打破所承受的痛苦，

169
00:11:32.632 --> 00:11:34.638
and he needed my compassion.
他需要我的同情。

170
00:11:35.857 --> 00:11:38.724
Keith was not able to be the one to speak up
基斯无法说出他的心声，

171
00:11:38.748 --> 00:11:41.238
and break our family money shame cycle,
打破我们家族金钱羞耻的循环，

172
00:11:41.262 --> 00:11:44.888
so he left me to do the work and share his legacy.
所以他留下我去做这项工作， 去分享他的遗产。

173
00:11:46.579 --> 00:11:48.206
Change is difficult,
改变很难，

174
00:11:49.612 --> 00:11:53.001
but in my family, not changing is fatal.
但在我的家庭中，不改变是致命的。

175
00:11:54.490 --> 00:11:56.144
So I did the work,
于是我做了这个工作，

176
00:11:56.168 --> 00:12:00.890
and I have experienced deep and profound forgiveness,
我经历了刻骨铭心的宽恕，

177
00:12:02.916 --> 00:12:05.297
and as I stand here today,
当今天我站在这里的时候，

178
00:12:05.321 --> 00:12:07.654
I am living on purpose,
我带着明确的目标生活着。

179
00:12:09.293 --> 00:12:12.356
I serve, and money serves me.
我服务社会，而金钱为我服务。

180
00:12:13.670 --> 00:12:17.828
It only takes one person in your family
只需要一个家人，

181
00:12:17.852 --> 00:12:20.328
to break through the money-shame cycle.
就可以打破家庭金钱羞耻的循环。

182
00:12:21.236 --> 00:12:23.597
I want you to be the one.
我希望你能成为这个人。

183
00:12:24.428 --> 00:12:25.579
Thank you.
谢谢。

184
00:12:25.603 --> 00:12:29.050
(Applause)
（鼓掌）